Tammy Petersen, News24L ckhoff High School in Idas Valley (Le Roux Schoeman, Netwerk24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Two girls captured on video assaulting fellow pupils at L&uuml;ckhoff High School in Idas Valley ,&nbsp;Stellenbosch,&nbsp;have been recommended for expulsion, the Western Cape Education Department said on Thursday. The school governing body made the recommendation following a disciplinary hearing attended by both girls on Wednesday, department spokesperson Jessica Shelver said. &nbsp;"It must be noted that it is only the head of a provincial education department who is afforded the power by law to expel a learner," she said.In the first case, a video of a pupil attacking another at the school on November 24 went viral on social media at the weekend.The girl, 15, appeared in the Stellenbosch Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Wednesday on a charge of assault with intent to inflict grievous bodily harm.The case was postponed to January 25 and transferred to the Child Justice Court for consultation and representations.On Tuesday, a second video surfaced of another girl assaulting a fellow pupil at the same school.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.